## 7. Quality Checklist

Before finalizing any report, verify:

### Content
- [ ] Summary clearly states purpose and key points
- [ ] All claims supported by data or logic
- [ ] Terminology used consistently
- [ ] No vague or ambiguous statements
- [ ] Recommendations are specific and actionable

### Structure
- [ ] Logical flow from background to conclusion
- [ ] Consistent heading hierarchy
- [ ] Appropriate use of lists and tables
- [ ] Visual elements enhance readability

### Style
- [ ] Nominal endings used consistently
- [ ] Professional and objective tone maintained
- [ ] No informal language or colloquialisms
- [ ] Sentences are concise and clear

### Formatting
- [ ] Consistent spacing and indentation
- [ ] Bold/italics used appropriately
- [ ] Horizontal rules separate major sections
- [ ] Metadata included at bottom

